<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAR 93 / London Stock Exchange: Strong debuts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The day's two newcomers to the stock market, Hambros Insurance Services
Group and Quality Software Products, put on very creditable first-day
showings.
The former was the market's third most heavily traded stock with some 15m
shares changing hands. The shares, oversubscribed almost four times, opened
at 146p, an 8p premium to the offer price of 138p, and moved in a relatively
narrow range to close at 144p. The shares attracted applications from 93
independent intermediaries - stockbrokers or financial advisers - more than
double the previous record for any flotation.
Quality Software quickly surged ahead to reach 537p, the eventual closing
level, for a premium of 41 per cent on the 380p issue price. Turnover was
1.3m shares.
</TEXT>
