<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAR 93 / Alcatel's Spanish arm in Polish purchase
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BOBINSKI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   WARSAW
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ALCATEL SESA, the Spanish arm of the French telecommunications group, has
agreed to pay Dollars 37.3m for Poland's PZT Telekom factory in Warsaw and
the Teletra plant in Poznan.
Alcatel will also invest Dollars 60m in the plants. The purchase opens the
way into Poland's domestic market for Alcatel as government regulations say
suppliers of telecommunications equipment have to produce at least half of
the value of any contracts.
The number of foreign bidders for contracts to supply telecommunications
equipment has been limited to three and each will have to have purchased
Polish plants. Next week the government is to chose between two rival bids
from Siemens and Northern Telecom for two further electronics plants, Elwro
in Wroclaw and Zwut in Warsaw.
This decision will in effect determine the identity of Poland's suppliers in
this sector for the foreseeable future as AT&amp;T has already bought the Telfa
plant in Bydgoszcz.
</TEXT>
