<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAR 93 / Mediobanca reports rise in pre-tax profits
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mediobanca, the Milan-based merchant bank, reported that profits for the
first six months of its 1992-93 financial year prior to tax, write-offs and
provisions rose slightly to L350.7bn from L340.4bn at the same time last
year.
Italian banks have recently reported heavy write-offs on securities holdings
and additional loan-loss provisions owing to the recession, implying that
the trend in Mediobanca's earnings may not be maintained when full-year
figures are reported in September.
</TEXT>
