<HEADLINE>
FT  31 MAR 93 / American Airlines joins fares war
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DANIEL GREEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AMERICAN Airlines triggered another round of transatlantic price cuts
yesterday by trimming another Pounds 10 from its economy fares between the
UK and the US. Its London to New York fare is now Pounds 249. It is also
offering Pounds 30 return fares for onward flights to some other US cities,
Daniel Green writes.
The cuts follow reductions announced last week by all the main airlines
linking the US and the UK. BA and Virgin Atlantic said they would not change
their tariffs in response to the move.
Virgin's fare is already Pounds 249, and BA said its Pounds 259 fare
includes a Pounds 10 security charge that is extra on the other airlines.
Virgin conceded that its customers pay Pounds 10 more than the published
fare.
