FT  31 MAR 93 / BT signs Pounds 40m supply deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN CANE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH Telecommunications and Racal-Datacom yesterday announced a strategic
alliance that could be worth up to Pounds 40m over three years to the data
communications company based in Reading, Berkshire.
Racal-Datacom has been named as BT's preferred supplier of networking
equipment and accompanying support services. The equipment involved in the
deal will include modems which enable computers to talk to each other over
telephone lines, multiplexers which enable several computers to share the
same telephone line simultaneously, and devices for integrated services
digital networks (ISDN), the most advanced data communications technology.
First product shipments are expected in June this year.
Mr Adam Scott, BT customer equipment director, said it was the most
important alliance so far in its sector.
Mr Tim Holley, Racal-Datacom group chairman, said the deal encompassed
everything from a simple link between two personal computers costing Pounds
1,000 to a multi-million-pound international network.
