FT  31 MAR 93 / Terrorist insurance criticism
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE ASSOCIATION of Risk Managers in Industry and Commerce yesterday
criticised the Association of British Insurers and the Department of Trade
and Industry for their response to providing cover for terrorist damage.
Speaking at the risk managers' annual conference, Ms Liz Taylor, who chairs
the risk managers, said Pool Re, the terrorist damage insurance pool, had
been devised without consultation with clients or brokers.
'Pool Re has been hastily conceived with considerable government
strictures,' she said. She added that the managing director had few
resources to assist his work.
But she called on her members to support Pool Re and warned that if they did
not there would be a serious risk it would founder.
She warned that the costs of the scheme might be excessive, and a number of
important issues about it remained unresolved.
