FT  30 MAR 93 / International Company News: Kleinwort sees China openings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TONY WALKER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
POWER generation projects for energy-starved China present almost boundless
opportunities for creative financing according to Mr Robin Fox,
vice-chairman of Kleinwort Benson, the UK merchant bank.
Mr Fox, speaking in Beijing at a Sino-British commercialisation and capital
project financing seminar, said 'build-operate-transfer' (BOT) deals would
help China overcome a shortfall of financing from traditional sources such
as the World Bank and Asian Development Bank. BOT schemes are infrastructure
projects built, operated and paid for by a promoter before transfer to
government ownership.
