<HEADLINE>
FT  30 MAR 93 / International Company News: Parmalat rises 24% to L52bn
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
PARMALAT, the Italian milk and dairy foods company, raised net group profits
by almost 24 per cent to L52bn (Dollars 32.9m) last year, due partly to a 23
per cent rise in sales to L1,636bn.
Mr Calisto Tanzi, chairman, said sales should reach about L2,800bn this
year, thanks to further acquisitions.
Acquisitions this year include a stake in Giglio, an Italian dairy group
with sales of about L400bn; Atlanta Dairy, a US dairy products concern with
about L100bn in turnover; Lacesa, a dairy products group; and the associated
Sodilac company in Brazil, with sales of about Dollars 80m.
</TEXT>
